4th July 2015 ITV4
19:00 to 20:00 Stage 1 Highlights

The 102nd Tour de France begins with a time trial at Utrecht in the Netherlands. Stage 1 is a flat course that takes in all the main sights of the city, and will give the strongest time-trialists the chance to pull on the first yellow jersey of this year's Tour. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary from Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting reporting at the roadside.
